<af:panelGroup>
  <af:outputText
    value="An applicant whose air contaminant source(s) meets the following 
    criteria may request in writing that the air contaminant source(s) be 
    issued an express permit-to-install (registration status). In order to be 
    considered for express permit-to-install processing (registration status), 
    the air contaminant source owner or operator must: "
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
   <af:objectSpacer height="1"/>
  <af:outputText
    value="(1) Submit a complete permit-to-install application,"
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
   <af:objectSpacer height="1"/>
  <af:outputText
    value="(2) Demonstrate compliance with all applicable law including the employment of BAT,"
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
   <af:objectSpacer height="1"/>
  <af:outputText
    value="(3) Have maximum uncontrolled emissions as defined in rule
    of the Wyoming Air Quality Standards and Regulations of less than five tons per each year for 
    particulate matter, sulfur dioxide,  nitrogen oxides, and OCs, "
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
   <af:objectSpacer height="1"/>
  <af:outputText
    value="(4) Not be subject to the United States 
    environmental protection agency new source performance standards, and"
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
   <af:objectSpacer height="1"/>
  <af:outputText
    value="(5) Not be subject to the national emission standards for hazardous air 
    pollutants or a United States environmental protection agency promulgated 
    standard for HAPs."
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
   <af:objectSpacer height="1"/>
  <af:outputText
    value="Within sixty days of the receipt of a complete request, 
    the director shall notify the applicant whether the air contaminant source 
    will be accepted for express permit-to-install processing (registration status). 
    Installation or construction of the air contaminant source may commence after 
    sixty days if the applicant has not been notified or upon the issuance of 
    the express permit-to-install (registration status)."
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
   <af:objectSpacer height="1"/>
  <af:outputText
    value="The issuance of an express permit-to-install (registration status) 
    does not relieve the  applicant from compliance with any applicable air pollution control 
    requirement (including the requirement to apply for a permit-to-operate) 
    and is at the discretion of the director."
    inlineStyle="font-size:75%;color:#666" />
</af:panelGroup>
